		<h1>Contact GNOME</h1>
		
		<h2>GNOME Foundation, Fundraising, Membership, and Press</h2>
		
		<p>Need to reach someone at the GNOME foundation?  You can contact the 
			GNOME community via email or by subscribing to an email list.</p>

		<dl>
			<dt><b>Email</b></dt>	
			<dd><a href="mailto:board@gnome.org">Board of Directors</a></dd>
			<dd><a href="mailto:director@gnome.org">Executive Director</a></dd>
			<dd><a href="mailto:membership-committee@gnome.org">Foundation Membership Committee</a></dd>
			<dd><a href="mailto:fundraising@gnome.org">Fundraising Committee</a></dd>
			<dd><a href="mailto:gnome-press-contact@gnome.org">Press Contact</a></dd>
			
			<dt><b>Email lists</b></dt>
			<dd><a href="http://mail.gnome.org/mailman/listinfo/foundation-list">Foundation mailing list</a></dd>
			<dd><a href="http://mail.gnome.org/mailman/listinfo/foundation-announce">Foundation Announce mailing list</a></dd>
			<dd><a href="http://mail.gnome.org/mailman/listinfo/fundraising-list">Fundraising mailing list</a></dd>
			
			<dt><b>Web sites</b></dt>
			<dd><a href="http://foundation.gnome.org/">Foundation Web site</a></dd>
			<dd><a href="http://foundation.gnome.org/membership.html">Foundation Membership Web site</a></dd>
			<dd><a href="http://www.gnome.org/friends/">Friend of GNOME Web site</a></dd>
			<dd><a href="http://www.gnome.org/press/">Press Contact Web site</a></dd>
			
			
		</dl>

		<h2>Related links</h2>

		<ul>
			<li>Getting Involved: becoming a <a href="http://developer.gnome.org/helping/">contributor to the GNOME Project</a></li>
			<li>Get Started: Information and installation instructions for the latest release of the  <a href="http://www.gnome.org/start/2.4/">GNOME Desktop &amp; Developer Platform</a></li>
		</ul>

		<h2>How to contact</h2>

		<p><strong>Email:</strong> Many GNOME email addresses are aliases that distribute your 
			email to several recipients.  You can learn who some of the recipients are from the appropriate Web site listed above.</p>

		<p><strong>Email lists:</strong> Lists manage and forward emails to a list of subscribed users
			who wish discuss the list's topic.
			There are a lot of GNOME-related mailing lists. You will find a 
			comprehensive list on the 
			<a href="http://mail.gnome.org/mailman/listinfo">gnome.org Mailman Lists</a> page, where you will also find instructions on how to subscribe and links to the archives of those lists.</p>

		<p><strong>Internet Relay Chat:</strong> 
			The <a href="http://www.irchelp.org/">IRC</a> network with the largest GNOME presence 
			is <a href="http://www.xach.com/gimpnet/">GIMPnet</a>, 
			with the channels #gnome-help (for getting help with GNOME) and 
			#gnome (for developer discussion) being the main resources.</p>

	</body>
